history.content:
Tech + Social Impact is an organization that aims to create a tight-knit community in which members can explore, have candid conversations about, and take action on ways to use technology for social good.

We are an organization looking to grow this semester, and we're looking for bright and motivated students to become tech project leaders and community event (such as speaker series) leaders and a financial director. You will have the opportunity to build and work on your passion projects. For last semester, we primarily focused on teaching a decal called "Technology and Social Impact", and worked on creating an app powered by ML to help people speak and communicate more effectively. 

Our short application is https://tinyurl.com/tsifa2021

 

We will also be having an info session next Monday 9/13 at 7PM and will be at Calapalooza this Thursday 9/9 from 5-7 pm.  Please let us know at techimpactberkeley@gmail.com if you have any questions!
